article.headline: Wyoming 97, Texas St. 96
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Brandon Ewing scored 27 points and Tyson Johnson added 22 to help Wyoming hold onto a 97-96 win over Texas State on Wednesday night. Adam Waddell and Afam Muojeke finished with 16 points apiece for the Cowboys (4-0). Wyoming seemed to have control of the game in the final seconds -- leading 97-93 with 4.5 seconds remaining. But Texas State's Brent Benson hit a 3-pointer and was fouled. He had a chance to tie the game, but his free throw came up empty. Benson, who was 9-of-13 from 3-point range, finished with a game-high 32 points for Texas State (2-2). Brandon Bush added 22 points, and Cameron Johnson chipped in 11.
